ntity, cultural background, class distinctions, and the right to be heard. Adding to the playful, raucous mood of the barb-trading birds is Armitage, who at one point inserts himself into the poem as a “magistrate . . . to adjudicate”—one who is “skilled with words & worldly wise / & frowns on every form of vice.”Featuring the Middle English text on facing pages and an introduction by Armitage, this volume will delight readers of all ages.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 0aBirdsvPoetry. 0aDebate poetry, English (Middle) 0aDebate poetry, English (Middle)vTranslations into English. 0aDebate poetry, English (Middle). 7aPOETRY / Medieval.2bisacsh  aAdultery.  aAge of the Earth.  aAge of the universe.  aAircraft.  aAlien Technology.  aAlien visitation.  aAlpha Centauri.  aApollo program.  aAptitude.  aAristotle.  aArthur C. Clarke.  aAstrology.  aAstronomer.  aAstronomy.  aAtomic number.  aAuthor.  aAuthorship.  aBaking.  aBillion years.  aChemical element.  aComplication (horology).  aCosmic microwave background.  aCourtesy.  aCrone.  aCrop circle.  aDesigner.  aDirge (Transformers).  aDisgust.  aDwarf planet.  aEarth's orbit.  aEarth.  aEmbarrassment.  aExoplanet.  aFoe (novel).  aGalileo Galilei.  aGeneral relativity.  aGenre.  aGeocentric model.  aGravity.  aHarassment.  aHoroscope.  aHour.  aHubble Space Telescope.  aIn Death.  aIndiscretion (Star Trek Deep Space Nine).  aIntention.  aInternational Astronomical Union.  aInterstellar medium.  aKepler's laws of planetary motion.  aLament.  aLight-year.  aLiterature.  aMartian.  aMedieval poetry.  aMercury (planet).  aMeteorite.  aMicroorganism.  aMicrosoft.  aMilitary aircraft.  aMisery (novel).  aMisfortune (folk tale).  aMonologue.  aMoo